Barcelona  defender Clement Lenglet is reportedly close to joining Tottenham on loan. The French centre back has fallen out of favour at the Spanish giants and is on the verge of agreeing a deal, but Spurs and manager Antonio Conte wants an answer soon. According to Mundo Deportivo, the North London side are the favourites to sign Lenglet, with Roma also interested, and Barcelona are also happy for the 27-year-old to leave on a temporary basis to help with financial fail play.